ontrol capability and the increasing preponderance of the government in essential sociopolitical affairs is becoming more and more frequently criticized. The essay analyses and evaluates this development. In the opinion of the author, the "open society of the lawmaker" and the tendency towards "de-institutionalization" of legislation are especially capable of endangering the freedom as well as the equality of the citizenry.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aInitiative, Right ofzGermany. 0aLegislative powerzGermany. 4aGesetzgebungslehre. 4aParlamentsrecht. 4aVerfassungsrecht. 7aLAW / Public.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Law - 2000 - 2014z9783110636208oZDB-23-GLA0 cprintz978389949173940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311091457340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110914573423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110914573/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-GLAc2000d2014